## 🧑🏾‍🏫 what this challenge teaches u
how to bypass httponly cookie attribute
httponly allows access to the cookie only from headers and not from javascript
the goal is:
  -once the victim sends a request to hacker, redirect to /ephemeral
  -in ephemeral, perform a reflected-xss in which the victim sends a fetch to / endpoint, saving the value to a variable
  -send this variable back to hacker's server as query string's value
the hard part was to write correctly the async function
since fetch is async, we have to specify await. but await can only exists inside a function.

